The Grumman Space Systems divisionof Grumman Corp is being awarded a 303.9 mln dlr Air Forcecontract for work related to the Strategic Defense Initiative(SDI), the Defense Department said.    It said the contract, similar to one awarded to LockheedCorp, is for a 34 month SDI Boost Surveillance and TrackingSystem demonstration/validation effort which is expected to becompleted in January 1990.    The department said 34.3 mln dlrs of the contract fundswill expire at the end of the current fiscal year. It addedthat 38 bids for the work were solicited and three proposalswere received. Reuter&#3;